{
  "decision_conditions": [
    "Reason : 1 - The London Borough of Hounslow as the Local Planning Authority hereby certify that on 04/11/2024, the proposal as shown on the drawing(s) submitted on 04/11/2024 and numbered 101 (P), 102 (P), 103 (P), 104 (P), 105 (P), 106 (P), 107 (P), 108 (P), 109 (P), 110 (P), 111 (P) was not lawful within the meanings of Section 191 and 192 of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990. \r\nThe development fails to comply with the terms of Class A, Clause A.1, (h) (i), Class A, Clause A1, (i) and Class A, Clause A1, (ja), of Part 1 of Schedule 2 of the Town and Country Planning (General Permitted Development) (England) Order 2015 (as amended) because the roof extension would attach to the an existing rear extension with a depth of more than 3 metres and a height of more than one storey, would be within 2 metres of the boundary with an eaves height of more than 3 metres, and the total enlargement would exceed the limits set out in sub-paragraphs (e) to (j).\r\n\r\nThe development also fails to comply with the terms of Class B, Clause B.2, (b) (i) (aa, bb) of Part 1 of Schedule 2 of the Town and Country Planning (General Permitted Development) (England) Order 2015 (as amended) because the roof extension which would attach to the existing rear extension would not maintain the eaves of the original roof, and would not be set up at least 0.2 metres from the eaves, measured along the roof slope.\r\n"
  ],
